From: conda-forge
Subject: [PATCH] Disable process jobs on Windows to avoid builderMainLoop error

GHC 9.2.8 bundles process-1.6.16.0 which has a bug in Windows job object
handling that can cause "builderMainLoop: invalid argument" errors when
spawning processes. This was fixed in process-1.6.18.0 ("Fix deadlock
when waiting for process completion and process jobs").

Since we cannot easily upgrade the bundled process library, this patch
disables the use_process_jobs feature on Windows to avoid the error.
This means GHC won't use job objects for process management, which is
fine for the conda-forge build environment.

See:
- https://hackage.haskell.org/package/process-1.6.24.0/changelog
- https://github.com/haskell/cabal/issues/7309
- https://gitlab.haskell.org/ghc/ghc/-/issues/18274

diff --git a/compiler/GHC/SysTools/Process.hs b/compiler/GHC/SysTools/Process.hs
--- a/compiler/GHC/SysTools/Process.hs
+++ b/compiler/GHC/SysTools/Process.hs
@@ -36,13 +36,17 @@ import System.Process

 import GHC.Utils.TmpFs

--- | Enable process jobs support on Windows if it can be expected to work (e.g.
--- @process >= 1.6.9.0@).
+-- | Enable process jobs support on Windows if it can be expected to work
+-- (e.g. @process >= 1.6.9.0@).
+-- CONDA-FORGE: Disabled on Windows due to builderMainLoop errors with
+-- process-1.6.16.0 bundled with GHC 9.2.8. The bug was fixed in process-1.6.18.0.
 enableProcessJobs :: CreateProcess -> CreateProcess
-#if defined(MIN_VERSION_process)
+#if defined(MIN_VERSION_process) && !defined(mingw32_HOST_OS)
 enableProcessJobs opts = opts { use_process_jobs = True }
 #else
+-- On Windows (mingw32_HOST_OS) or when process version is unknown,
+-- don't enable process jobs to avoid "builderMainLoop: invalid argument" errors
 enableProcessJobs opts = opts
 #endif

